                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_k0yrdaʒ" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>k˳yrdaʒ</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kurdbaʒæ</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>кузница</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>smithery</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ew sæwmæ Ajsana Kurd-Alægoni kurdbaʒæmæ bacudæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в одно утро Айсана вошел в кузницу Курд-Алагона</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>one morning Aisana entered the Kurd-Alagon forge</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 43</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>k˳yrdaʒy... ærra Besæ fsæjnægtæ xojy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в кузнице безумный Беса колотит по железу</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Crazy Besa is pounding iron in his forge</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>74</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ew sæwmæ Ajsana Kurd-Alægoni kurdbaʒæmæ bacudæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в одно утро Айсана вошел в кузницу Курд-Алагона</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>one morning Aisana entered the Kurd-Alagon forge</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 43</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>k˳yrdaʒy... ærra Besæ fsæjnægtæ xojy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в кузнице безумный Беса колотит по железу</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Crazy Besa is pounding iron in his forge</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>74</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Буквально „место (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_baʒæ"/>) кузнеца (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_kurd"/>)ʼ. Для второй части (%i-aʒ%i | %i-baʒæ%i) ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kærdbaʒæ"/> ‘ножны’, а также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mydaʒ"/> ‘воск’ и, может быть, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wælaʒyg"/> (%iwæl-aʒ-yg%i) ‘этаж’.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Literally „a place (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_baʒæ"/>) of a blacksmith (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_kurd"/>)ʼ. For the second part (%i-aʒ%i | %i-baʒæ%i) cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kærdbaʒæ"/> ‘scabbard’, and also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mydaʒ"/> ‘wax’ and, maybe, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wælaʒyg"/> (%iwæl-aʒ-yg%i) ‘storey’.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>